BFN 

  [Text] Chechnya President Dzhokhar Dudayev's wife and young 
son received injuries of varying degrees of severity during the 
assassination attempt on the president on 28 May, according to a 
statement released by the Chechnya Foreign Ministry today. The 
Foreign Ministry assesses the act of terrorism, in which the 
republic's interior minister and his deputy were killed, as an 
attack on President Dudayev. The terrorists used a 
remote-control explosive device, which the Russian special 
services have at their disposal. 

